         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25/1/62 ¶ Dear Mr Bentham ¶  ¶ In writing to you yesterday ¶  I forgot to direct your attention to the curious form of the anthers of Hibbertia stellaris, Endl. Perhaps you may have overlooked it. To ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.01.25b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller,1858-70, f. 53.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-<seg style="color: #000000; ">edged. M's sister Bertha died on 7 September 1861.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>25/1/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Bentham</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In writing to you yesterday<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to G. Bentham, 24 January 1862.</p>
               </note> I forgot to direct your attention to the curious form of the anthers of <name key="Hibbertia%20stellaris">Hibbertia stellaris</name>, Endl. Perhaps you may have overlooked it. To me it seems important, since you attach generic value to <name key="Adrastaea">Adrastaea</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">See G. Bentham to M, 16 November 1861.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I speak from memory, since the <name key="Dilleniaceae">Dilleniaceae</name> are on the way to you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Attached</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Adrastaea">Adrastaea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dilleniaceae">Dilleniaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hibbertia%20stellaris">Hibbertia stellaris</name>
            </p>
